Journal Story: Â Started the first day with overcast skies and sleet. Hopefully tomorrow will be a better day.

Snow started about 1:00pm. Got about 4 inches of snow today through about 9:00pm. Received some trail magic from the 12 Tribes. They had to hike about 
1 1/2 miles up the Mountain in the snow and dark to reach us.

Made it to Neel Gap. Having a lot of problems with my knees and calves. Going home to recoup for a short time. Restarting North bound at Watuga Lake. Will have to make up the miles South of Watuga Lake after finishing the Northbound Trail
Staying at Braemar Hostel tonight. It is pouring down rain. Starting the trail tomorrow morning at Watauga Lake.
Steep terrain. Took 9 hours to go 9 miles. Definitely going to sleep good tonight.
Had enough. Will be a day hiker in the future. I will not hike again caring a full backpack. Good Luck to all the hikers out there.
Destination: Rt. TN 91 at the Piped Spring
